Q19.To insert text before and after an image using jQuery. [Hint: Use before() and after()] 

Answer:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
<html>
<head>
<script src="jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>

	<script>
		$(document).ready(function(){
			$("img").before("rbnb");
			$("img").after("college");
		});
	</script>
</head>
<body>
	<img src="paste img link">
</body>
</html>
